prompt.user:
Project: {project_name} Client: {client_name} Methodology: {methodology} Service Lines: {service_lines}
Project Type Guidance: {project_type_guidance}
SOW Summary: {sow_summary}
Service Line Design Standards: {standards_context}
Platform Combination Patterns (proven integration patterns for this service line mix): {combinations_context}
Generated Requirements Context (if available): {requirements_context}
FORMAT GUIDE ONLY — READ CAREFULLY BEFORE GENERATING: The example below is for a COMPLETELY DIFFERENT fictional project (Meridian Insurance). DO NOT copy any of the following from the example into your output: - Names (Meridian, CaseEscalationEvent__e, CaseToIncidentFlow, SalesforceRepository) - Specific numbers (3 outages, 5 failures, 60 seconds) - Requirement IDs (FR-INT-001) unless they also appear in THIS project's requirements context above - Any file paths or class names from the example The example shows ONLY the depth and structure of justification required. All content must come from the actual project context above.
FORMAT EXAMPLE (fictional project — structure only):
### Pattern: [Pattern Name] - **Category**: [Creational / Structural / Behavioral / Integration / Resilience] - **Why this project**: [Specific reason tied to an actual requirement ID or SOW constraint from the project context above — name the exact FR/NFR that drives this pattern, or the specific platform limitation that makes this pattern necessary] - **Where applied**: [Actual class/file name relevant to this project's service lines — e.g. if Salesforce: an Apex class name; if ServiceNow: a Script Include name] - **Implementation guide**: [Concrete implementation steps using actual platform APIs for the service lines in this project]
END OF FORMAT EXAMPLE.
Now identify and justify design patterns for {project_name} — client {client_name}, service lines: {service_lines}. Every "Why this project" must quote an actual requirement ID or SOW detail from the context above — not invented details. Name actual component files using the correct naming conventions for the service lines above. Do not copy any names or numbers from the format example. Do NOT add a "Note:" section or any closing assumptions paragraph. Output ONLY markdown.
